00:38:03.980 --> 00:38:06.050 align:middle line:84%
I have to share this
with someone else.

00:38:06.050 --> 00:38:08.450 align:middle line:84%
Can you see how I believe
our children are our greatest

00:38:08.450 --> 00:38:10.914 align:middle line:90%
teachers?

00:38:10.914 --> 00:38:11.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Of course I can.

00:38:11.850 --> 00:38:15.165 align:middle line:90%
>> I nearly got emotional there.

00:38:15.165 --> 00:38:16.610 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, wow.

00:38:16.610 --> 00:38:21.440 align:middle line:84%
Well I mean, it's a real
interesting circle of life

00:38:21.440 --> 00:38:23.930 align:middle line:84%
isn't it, because I think
my whole line of work

00:38:23.930 --> 00:38:25.940 align:middle line:84%
over the last 12 or
15 years was really

00:38:25.940 --> 00:38:27.710 align:middle line:90%
an impetus to help my dad.

00:38:27.710 --> 00:38:30.960 align:middle line:84%
And then for me to
realize that wow,

00:38:30.960 --> 00:38:34.230 align:middle line:84%
we're helping each other in so
many ways, we're like a team.

00:38:34.230 --> 00:38:35.030 align:middle line:90%
He's needed me.

00:38:35.030 --> 00:38:37.370 align:middle line:90%
I've needed him.

00:38:37.370 --> 00:38:40.590 align:middle line:90%
>> I've had people say, why me?

00:38:40.590 --> 00:38:42.493 align:middle line:84%
Why do I have to
go through this?

00:38:42.493 --> 00:38:43.910 align:middle line:84%
Your dad could say
the same thing.

00:38:43.910 --> 00:38:45.350 align:middle line:90%
Why me?

00:38:45.350 --> 00:38:48.170 align:middle line:90%
So many people can say, why me?

00:38:48.170 --> 00:38:50.390 align:middle line:90%
I say, why not you?

00:38:50.390 --> 00:38:51.662 align:middle line:90%
What have you got for me?

00:38:51.662 --> 00:38:53.120 align:middle line:10%
What have you got
for the universe?

00:38:53.120 --> 00:38:55.820 align:middle line:84%
How are you going to show up
so that you can teach others

00:38:55.820 --> 00:38:58.860 align:middle line:84%
how they can do this with
courage and grace and strength

00:38:58.860 --> 00:38:59.660 align:middle line:90%
and dignity?

00:38:59.660 --> 00:39:02.024 align:middle line:10%
Why not you?

00:39:02.024 --> 00:39:04.830 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:39:04.830 --> 00:39:09.410 align:middle line:84%
You talk about four
agreements in your book.

00:39:09.410 --> 00:39:11.450 align:middle line:84%
Can you explain that a
little bit more for me?

00:39:11.450 --> 00:39:14.605 align:middle line:84%
>> It had such a profound
impact on me, that book.

00:39:14.605 --> 00:39:15.980 align:middle line:84%
The four agreements--
number one,

00:39:15.980 --> 00:39:18.090 align:middle line:90%
be impeccable with your word.

00:39:18.090 --> 00:39:20.940 align:middle line:90%
Number two-- ask questions.

00:39:20.940 --> 00:39:22.370 align:middle line:90%
Don't make assumptions.

00:39:22.370 --> 00:39:24.900 align:middle line:84%
Number three-- don't
take things personally.

00:39:24.900 --> 00:39:27.860 align:middle line:84%
And number four--
always give your best.

00:39:27.860 --> 00:39:30.530 align:middle line:90%
I believe in Don's work.

00:39:30.530 --> 00:39:33.510 align:middle line:84%
If we could all live by
those four agreements,

00:39:33.510 --> 00:39:35.540 align:middle line:84%
I don't think we'd
be needing to talk

00:39:35.540 --> 00:39:38.900 align:middle line:84%
about why self-love is such
a difficult concept for so

00:39:38.900 --> 00:39:40.070 align:middle line:90%
many people.

00:39:40.070 --> 00:39:44.120 align:middle line:84%
And I agree that if we could
even just take the don't take

00:39:44.120 --> 00:39:47.630 align:middle line:84%
things personally, if we could
just take that one on, it would

00:39:47.630 --> 00:39:51.650 align:middle line:84%
be a game changer in the way
you believe in yourself. .

00:39:51.650 --> 00:39:53.960 align:middle line:84%
Everyone's a-- my
husband played cricket

00:39:53.960 --> 00:39:56.030 align:middle line:90%
for New Zealand for 10 years.

00:39:56.030 --> 00:39:57.770 align:middle line:84%
And I'm not sure
if I can say this.

00:39:57.770 --> 00:40:00.560 align:middle line:84%
But his line was, "Opinions
are like assholes.

00:40:00.560 --> 00:40:02.020 align:middle line:90%
Everybody's got one."

00:40:02.020 --> 00:40:04.910 align:middle line:84%
And I used to think,
oh, that was so harsh.

00:40:04.910 --> 00:40:06.260 align:middle line:90%
But I would read the paper.

00:40:06.260 --> 00:40:08.060 align:middle line:84%
And he'd go, don't
worry about it.

00:40:08.060 --> 00:40:09.830 align:middle line:84%
And I love what
Ricky Gervais says.

00:40:09.830 --> 00:40:12.080 align:middle line:84%
"These people don't come
home and have dinner with me.

00:40:12.080 --> 00:40:13.500 align:middle line:90%
Don't worry about it."

00:40:13.500 --> 00:40:15.208 align:middle line:84%
I think it's really
important that people

00:40:15.208 --> 00:40:16.625 align:middle line:84%
are-- there are
going to be people

00:40:16.625 --> 00:40:17.870 align:middle line:90%
that want to have opinions.

00:40:17.870 --> 00:40:20.940 align:middle line:84%
And they're going to
give you attacks, maybe.

00:40:20.940 --> 00:40:22.940 align:middle line:84%
Or they're going to say
things that aren't nice.

00:40:22.940 --> 00:40:25.550 align:middle line:84%
Or perhaps they're going to
say things that really hurt.

00:40:25.550 --> 00:40:28.160 align:middle line:84%
But to turn it around-- and
one of the key things that I

00:40:28.160 --> 00:40:32.630 align:middle line:84%
took from that is if
someone says you're useless

00:40:32.630 --> 00:40:35.180 align:middle line:84%
or you're hopeless and
they're saying that

00:40:35.180 --> 00:40:38.420 align:middle line:84%
or I'm hearing those words,
one of the tools that I took on

00:40:38.420 --> 00:40:41.360 align:middle line:84%
was actually just
replace you with I.

00:40:41.360 --> 00:40:45.290 align:middle line:84%
So they're actually saying
I'm useless or I'm hopeless.

00:40:45.290 --> 00:40:48.560 align:middle line:84%
And that's been a really
good game changer for me

00:40:48.560 --> 00:40:50.180 align:middle line:90%
because it's true.

00:40:50.180 --> 00:40:53.060 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't say those things
unless I had been that

00:40:53.060 --> 00:40:56.450 align:middle line:84%
or unless I believe that or
I was behaving like that.

00:40:56.450 --> 00:40:58.700 align:middle line:84%
I think it's really important
to know that people will

00:40:58.700 --> 00:41:00.830 align:middle line:84%
say things, and it's
more a reflection

00:41:00.830 --> 00:41:03.950 align:middle line:84%
on what they're thinking and
feeling than it is about you.

00:41:03.950 --> 00:41:07.640 align:middle line:84%
If you could learn to create
a beautiful rebounding

00:41:07.640 --> 00:41:09.770 align:middle line:84%
shield that just turned
it back into whenever

00:41:09.770 --> 00:41:12.740 align:middle line:84%
they say you, say
I, that's become

00:41:12.740 --> 00:41:14.840 align:middle line:90%
my own protective shield.

00:41:14.840 --> 00:41:19.010 align:middle line:84%
And if there's still a charge
associated to taking something

00:41:19.010 --> 00:41:22.520 align:middle line:84%
personally, then go after the
why I'm feeling the charge,

00:41:22.520 --> 00:41:23.960 align:middle line:90%
not what they said.

00:41:23.960 --> 00:41:25.220 align:middle line:90%
That's the real work.

00:41:25.220 --> 00:41:27.830 align:middle line:84%
Why am I still having a
charge around that comment?

00:41:27.830 --> 00:41:31.100 align:middle line:10%
What can I do about it
to work on it for myself?

00:41:31.100 --> 00:41:33.230 align:middle line:84%
There's a beautiful
statement-- my business,

00:41:33.230 --> 00:41:35.390 align:middle line:84%
your business, and
universal business.

00:41:35.390 --> 00:41:38.450 align:middle line:10%
My business is how I
behave in life, what I say,

00:41:38.450 --> 00:41:42.320 align:middle line:10%
my actions, my judgments, my
perceptions, my behaviors.

00:41:42.320 --> 00:41:43.880 align:middle line:10%
They're all my business.

00:41:43.880 --> 00:41:47.150 align:middle line:10%
Your business is how you behave,
act, your opinions, and all

00:41:47.150 --> 00:41:48.560 align:middle line:10%
the things that you do.

00:41:48.560 --> 00:41:52.670 align:middle line:84%
And then there's universal
business, flowers growing,

00:41:52.670 --> 00:41:55.790 align:middle line:84%
the wind blowing, planes
falling out of the sky,

00:41:55.790 --> 00:41:56.870 align:middle line:90%
volcanoes erupting.

00:41:56.870 --> 00:41:59.060 align:middle line:90%
There's universal business.

00:41:59.060 --> 00:42:02.480 align:middle line:84%
It's none of my business
what you think of me.

00:42:02.480 --> 00:42:07.200 align:middle line:10%
And that's also been a
really beautiful tool for me,

00:42:07.200 --> 00:42:08.930 align:middle line:10%
particularly the
more out there I

00:42:08.930 --> 00:42:12.200 align:middle line:10%
am with speaking and
teaching and sharing

00:42:12.200 --> 00:42:16.587 align:middle line:10%
myself so openly and so
vulnerably, that sometimes--

00:42:16.587 --> 00:42:18.170 align:middle line:10%
you know, I got given
a quote one day.

00:42:18.170 --> 00:42:21.140 align:middle line:84%
You can be the juiciest,
ripest, most succulent peach

00:42:21.140 --> 00:42:25.010 align:middle line:84%
on the tree, and some people
just don't like peaches.

00:42:25.010 --> 00:42:28.790 align:middle line:84%
And I think that is a beautiful
way of looking at life.

00:42:28.790 --> 00:42:31.080 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to get
on with everybody.

00:42:31.080 --> 00:42:33.170 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to be
everyone's friends.

00:42:33.170 --> 00:42:34.850 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes that
beautiful quote--

00:42:34.850 --> 00:42:37.070 align:middle line:84%
a reason, a season,
and a lifetime--

00:42:37.070 --> 00:42:40.610 align:middle line:84%
could not be more profound than
in doing this work of being

00:42:40.610 --> 00:42:41.662 align:middle line:90%
a human being.

00:42:41.662 --> 00:42:43.370 align:middle line:84%
There are people that
come into our lives

00:42:43.370 --> 00:42:46.010 align:middle line:84%
for a reason, some for a
season, and then there's

00:42:46.010 --> 00:42:49.280 align:middle line:84%
some beautiful souls who
stay with us for a lifetime.

00:42:49.280 --> 00:42:51.620 align:middle line:84%
And I think if we can
appreciate that life

00:42:51.620 --> 00:42:55.940 align:middle line:84%
is full of joys and challenges,
friends that will be here

00:42:55.940 --> 00:42:57.500 align:middle line:84%
forever, and some
that won't be there

00:42:57.500 --> 00:43:00.480 align:middle line:84%
for very long, that there's
happiness and there's sadness.

00:43:00.480 --> 00:43:02.480 align:middle line:10%
There's times when we
feel great about ourselves

00:43:02.480 --> 00:43:04.980 align:middle line:10%
and there's times where we don't
feel great about ourselves.

00:43:04.980 --> 00:43:07.460 align:middle line:84%
If we could just come to a
beautiful place of acceptance

00:43:07.460 --> 00:43:10.940 align:middle line:84%
in realizing that life is
a constant ultramarathon

00:43:10.940 --> 00:43:13.160 align:middle line:84%
and there's times where
we're going to be chafed,

00:43:13.160 --> 00:43:15.952 align:middle line:84%
hurt, sore, and blisters,
and then there's

00:43:15.952 --> 00:43:17.660 align:middle line:84%
times when we've pulled
muscles, and then

00:43:17.660 --> 00:43:21.170 align:middle line:84%
there's times when literally it
is important to quit the race

00:43:21.170 --> 00:43:22.520 align:middle line:90%
and start a new one--

00:43:22.520 --> 00:43:25.250 align:middle line:84%
if we can just understand
it's all a beautiful tapestry

00:43:25.250 --> 00:43:27.202 align:middle line:84%
of what it means to
be a human being,

00:43:27.202 --> 00:43:28.910 align:middle line:84%
then maybe we'd give
ourselves permission

00:43:28.910 --> 00:43:31.430 align:middle line:84%
