And that's great
on the good days.

00:46:21.860 --> 00:46:24.200 align:middle line:84%
But I also believe in being
authentic and integral

00:46:24.200 --> 00:46:25.630 align:middle line:90%
in the days that aren't so good.

00:46:25.630 --> 00:46:28.130 align:middle line:84%
So when you do that ritual on
a day where you're not feeling

00:46:28.130 --> 00:46:30.225 align:middle line:84%
so great, then when
you get to the part

00:46:30.225 --> 00:46:32.600 align:middle line:84%
where you take three deep
breaths and say something nice,

00:46:32.600 --> 00:46:35.930 align:middle line:84%
then that is the day I
will say I'm just grateful

00:46:35.930 --> 00:46:37.460 align:middle line:90%
I'm breathing.

00:46:37.460 --> 00:46:39.290 align:middle line:90%
The sun is shining.

00:46:39.290 --> 00:46:40.610 align:middle line:90%
I've got this.

00:46:40.610 --> 00:46:44.540 align:middle line:84%
Or it might be asking
god, source, universe,

00:46:44.540 --> 00:46:48.530 align:middle line:84%
give me the courage,
grace, strength, dignity,

00:46:48.530 --> 00:46:51.408 align:middle line:84%
and amazing ability
to get through this.

00:46:51.408 --> 00:46:53.450 align:middle line:84%
So I think it's about
being authentic when you're

00:46:53.450 --> 00:46:56.140 align:middle line:90%
going through tough times.

00:46:56.140 --> 00:46:58.910 align:middle line:84%
Putting a half a
lemon into your water

00:46:58.910 --> 00:47:00.770 align:middle line:84%
may seem like such
a simple ritual,

00:47:00.770 --> 00:47:03.020 align:middle line:84%
but it is such a
cleansing thing to do.

00:47:03.020 --> 00:47:05.750 align:middle line:84%
The metaphor of taking
water to cleanse,

00:47:05.750 --> 00:47:09.110 align:middle line:84%
and lemon to help cleanse
your digestive system, also

00:47:09.110 --> 00:47:11.600 align:middle line:84%
helps cleanse negative
thoughts and thinking.

00:47:11.600 --> 00:47:14.660 align:middle line:84%
Walking outside with a drop
of frankincense on a tissue

00:47:14.660 --> 00:47:18.470 align:middle line:84%
and taking three deep breaths
in bare feet touching the Earth

00:47:18.470 --> 00:47:20.720 align:middle line:84%
is a great way to
connect us to source,

00:47:20.720 --> 00:47:25.730 align:middle line:84%
or at least reach out and ask
for some guidance and support.

00:47:25.730 --> 00:47:30.150 align:middle line:84%
I believe in going
out walking in nature,

00:47:30.150 --> 00:47:32.600 align:middle line:84%
even if it's out on
a walk on concrete.

00:47:32.600 --> 00:47:34.880 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes for me when I
go out running or jogging,

00:47:34.880 --> 00:47:36.330 align:middle line:90%
sometimes it hurts.

00:47:36.330 --> 00:47:39.210 align:middle line:84%
And instead of giving up and
going oh, I can't do this,

00:47:39.210 --> 00:47:42.290 align:middle line:84%
I've got a mantra that I say
every time any part of me

00:47:42.290 --> 00:47:46.395 align:middle line:84%
hurts, my heart included,
when I'm out walking in nature

00:47:46.395 --> 00:47:47.270 align:middle line:90%
or running in nature.

00:47:47.270 --> 00:47:49.780 align:middle line:84%
And that is, every
step I take, I

00:47:49.780 --> 00:47:51.890 align:middle line:84%
am connected to
you, Mother Earth.

00:47:51.890 --> 00:47:54.690 align:middle line:10%
Every breath I take, I'm aware
of my thoughts, feelings,

00:47:54.690 --> 00:47:56.000 align:middle line:10%
and emotions.

00:47:56.000 --> 00:47:59.240 align:middle line:84%
And I am proud, privileged,
and honored to be out here

00:47:59.240 --> 00:48:01.850 align:middle line:84%
on behalf of all
of those who can't.

00:48:01.850 --> 00:48:04.520 align:middle line:84%
And it reminds me that there's
people that would give anything

00:48:04.520 --> 00:48:06.160 align:middle line:84%
to be out here
walking in nature,

00:48:06.160 --> 00:48:08.660 align:middle line:84%
or there's people out there
that would love two healthy legs

00:48:08.660 --> 00:48:11.480 align:middle line:84%
to walk, or there's people
who are so broken-hearted they

00:48:11.480 --> 00:48:13.560 align:middle line:90%
can't even breathe right now.

00:48:13.560 --> 00:48:15.860 align:middle line:84%
So part of my giving
back to humanity

00:48:15.860 --> 00:48:18.110 align:middle line:84%
is honoring all
those people in pain

00:48:18.110 --> 00:48:20.690 align:middle line:84%
through my own daily
self-care rituals.

00:48:20.690 --> 00:48:24.320 align:middle line:84%
It can be something as
simple as a spritzer,

00:48:24.320 --> 00:48:25.940 align:middle line:84%
filling a little
bottle with water

00:48:25.940 --> 00:48:28.250 align:middle line:84%
and adding six drops of
essential oil to that.

00:48:28.250 --> 00:48:29.780 align:middle line:90%
And I have them in the car.

00:48:29.780 --> 00:48:30.880 align:middle line:90%
I have them in my handbag.

00:48:30.880 --> 00:48:32.852 align:middle line:84%
I have them in the fridge
on hot, sunny days.

00:48:32.852 --> 00:48:34.810 align:middle line:84%
I had them beside the
bed when I say good night

00:48:34.810 --> 00:48:36.370 align:middle line:90%
to my children who are still--

00:48:36.370 --> 00:48:37.510 align:middle line:90%
they're now adult children.

00:48:37.510 --> 00:48:39.850 align:middle line:84%
I still aromatically
spritz and kiss

00:48:39.850 --> 00:48:40.990 align:middle line:90%
them goodnight every night.

00:48:40.990 --> 00:48:43.870 align:middle line:84%
They'll get a little spritz
with some calming oils.

00:48:43.870 --> 00:48:48.160 align:middle line:84%
And I guess I call them
aromatic anchors, ways in which

00:48:48.160 --> 00:48:50.440 align:middle line:84%
to anchor yourself to
the truth, to the core,

00:48:50.440 --> 00:48:53.350 align:middle line:84%
to the rawness of
where I'm at right now,

00:48:53.350 --> 00:48:56.500 align:middle line:84%
by giving me something to do
so that I can get through it.

00:48:56.500 --> 00:48:58.780 align:middle line:84%
I think all of these
little rituals and anything

00:48:58.780 --> 00:49:02.710 align:middle line:84%
to do with nature, food,
breath, meditation--

00:49:02.710 --> 00:49:03.850 align:middle line:90%
oh my gosh.

00:49:03.850 --> 00:49:06.520 align:middle line:84%
You see, when you're feeling
down and out sometimes sitting

00:49:06.520 --> 00:49:11.020 align:middle line:84%
there meditating is the last
thing you've got the courage

00:49:11.020 --> 00:49:13.150 align:middle line:84%
to do because the
monkey brain kicks in

00:49:13.150 --> 00:49:15.520 align:middle line:84%
or we don't feel good
about it or whatever.

00:49:15.520 --> 00:49:17.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, after reading
Thich Nhat Hanh's book,

00:49:17.650 --> 00:49:21.010 align:middle line:84%
this Tibetan Buddhist monk,
he talks about being mindful.

00:49:21.010 --> 00:49:22.840 align:middle line:84%
So even as you're
cutting a tomato

00:49:22.840 --> 00:49:27.280 align:middle line:84%
to put on your paleo bread for
lunch, as you're cutting it

00:49:27.280 --> 00:49:30.160 align:middle line:84%
and you look at the tomato and
think about the farmer that

00:49:30.160 --> 00:49:32.350 align:middle line:84%
grew it that you bought
from your farmers markets

00:49:32.350 --> 00:49:35.310 align:middle line:84%
that morning, looking at the
four chambers of that tomato

00:49:35.310 --> 00:49:36.910 align:middle line:84%
as you're cutting
it, and realizing

00:49:36.910 --> 00:49:39.290 align:middle line:84%
that the nutrients
in that tomato

00:49:39.290 --> 00:49:42.070 align:middle line:84%
are talking to you in
the shape that tomatoes

00:49:42.070 --> 00:49:44.365 align:middle line:84%
are wonderful for the
heart, we call that

00:49:44.365 --> 00:49:45.490 align:middle line:90%
the doctrine of signatures.

00:49:45.490 --> 00:49:48.400 align:middle line:84%
Plants and foods are
constantly talking to us.

00:49:48.400 --> 00:49:50.590 align:middle line:84%
Just even saying
that or being mindful

00:49:50.590 --> 00:49:53.050 align:middle line:84%
of how a walnut
looks like the brain

00:49:53.050 --> 00:49:55.690 align:middle line:84%
is mindfulness,
which is meditation.

00:49:55.690 --> 00:49:59.350 align:middle line:84%
So you don't have to sit
there for an hour saying ohm.

00:49:59.350 --> 00:50:02.150 align:middle line:84%
It could just simply taking
a deep breath and saying,

00:50:02.150 --> 00:50:03.320 align:middle line:90%
I am love.

00:50:03.320 --> 00:50:04.660 align:middle line:90%
That is meditation.

00:50:04.660 --> 00:50:07.870 align:middle line:84%
And I think as a busy
woman, a mom, and anyone

00:50:07.870 --> 00:50:10.060 align:middle line:84%
out there who is frantic
in life or feeling

00:50:10.060 --> 00:50:12.310 align:middle line:84%
like life is frantic
to them, then

00:50:12.310 --> 00:50:15.790 align:middle line:84%
it's those small what I call
micromoments of mindfulness

00:50:15.790 --> 00:50:17.500 align:middle line:90%
that is an act of self-care.

00:50:17.500 --> 00:50:20.410 align:middle line:90%
It's about space, silence.

00:50:20.410 --> 00:50:24.070 align:middle line:84%
It's about giving yourself that
solitude, those moments that

00:50:24.070 --> 00:50:27.880 align:middle line:84%
will help refill your
cup so that you can

00:50:27.880 --> 00:50:29.710 align:middle line:90%
get through the next breath.

00:50:29.710 --> 00:50:33.730 align:middle line:84%
I always say, moment by moment,
breath by breath, day by day,

00:50:33.730 --> 00:50:34.960 align:middle line:90%
I've got this.

00:50:34.960 --> 00:50:36.877 align:middle line:84%
And even in the moments
I haven't, I will then

00:50:36.877 --> 00:50:39.252 align:middle line:84%
remind myself I just got
through that moment, so in fact,

00:50:39.252 --> 00:50:40.090 align:middle line:90%
I have.

00:50:40.090 --> 00:50:41.410 align:middle line:90%
I'm still here.

00:50:41.410 --> 00:50:42.880 align:middle line:90%
You are still here.

00:50:42.880 --> 00:50:45.340 align:middle line:84%
You have got through the
worst moments in your life.

00:50:45.340 --> 00:50:46.300 align:middle line:90%
You're still here.

00:50:46.300 --> 00:50:49.060 align:middle line:84%
Therefore, in hindsight
when we look back

00:50:49.060 --> 00:50:51.880 align:middle line:84%
at those times that have been
really challenging, I would

00:50:51.880 --> 00:50:55.360 align:middle line:84%
almost suggest that anything
that's been challenging to you

00:50:55.360 --> 00:50:58.270 align:middle line:84%
in your life that you look back
on, when you look back on it

00:50:58.270 --> 00:51:01.450 align:middle line:84%
with hindsight, you could
almost say, yes, it was a gift.

00:51:01.450 --> 00:51:04.600 align:middle line:84%
Or, it is because of
that I have actually

00:51:04.600 --> 00:51:07.000 align:middle line:84%
created this in my life,
or I've become that,

00:51:07.000 --> 00:51:10.600 align:middle line:84%
or I have met this person,
or I have studied that.

00:51:10.600 --> 00:51:13.027 align:middle line:84%
There is a gift in
every challenge.

00:51:13.027 --> 00:51:14.860 align:middle line:84%
It's just whether or
not we're willing to be

00:51:14.860 --> 00:51:16.930 align:middle line:84%
open to having the
perception that we

00:51:16.930 --> 00:51:19.750 align:middle line:84%
deserve the truth
and the pathway

00:51:19.750 --> 00:51:22.190 align:middle line:84%
to finding that
new way of being.

00:51:22.190 --> 00:51:25.480 align:middle line:84%
And I can tell you, it is
through the powerful mastery

00:51:25.480 --> 00:51:28.690 align:middle line:84%
of our spiritual leaders
that they will also

00:51:28.690 --> 00:51:31.090 align:middle line:84%
say that that is
part of the pathway.

00:51:31.090 --> 00:51:37.770 align:middle line:84%
Struggle is the pathway to self,
to god, to universe, to source.

00:51:37.770 --> 00:51:40.150 align:middle line:84%
>> Kim, you are
a force for good.

00:51:40.150 --> 00:51:41.900 align:middle line:90%
You're a force for god.

00:51:41.900 --> 00:51:44.470 align:middle line:84%
And I'm so grateful to have
you as a friend in my life

00:51:44.470 --> 00:51:46.303 align:middle line:84%
even though I don't get
to catch up with you

00:51:46.303 --> 00:51:47.740 align:middle line:90%
as much as I'd like to--

00:51:47.740 --> 00:51:49.240 align:middle line:90%
hopefully more.

00:51:49.240 --> 00:51:50.960 align:middle line:84%
And thank you so much
